{%- comment -%}
  sections/cart-recommendations.liquid
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  PURPOSE
    Thin wrapper around snippets/product-recommendations.liquid.
    Exists solely so the Section Rendering API can re-render recommendations
    independently of the main cart-drawer section.

  HOW IT IS FETCHED
    cart-recommendations.js calls:

      GET /?section_id=cart-recommendations
            &product_id={last_cart_product_id}
            &intent={complementary|related}
            &limit={n}

    The Product Recommendations API endpoint is called server-side here,
    so there is no CORS concern and the response is cacheable at the CDN.

  SECTION RENDERING INTEGRATION
    assets/cart-recommendations.js swaps [data-ecd-recs-container] innerHTML
    with the full HTML response from this section fetch.

  PARAMETERS (via URL query string — Liquid reads them from request object)
    product_id   {Number}  The product ID to base recommendations on.
                           Falls back to the last item in the current cart.
    intent       {String}  'complementary' or 'related'. Default: 'complementary'.
    limit        {Number}  Max recommendations to fetch. Default: 6 (JS trims to 4
                           after excluding cart items, so we over-fetch slightly).

  WHY OVER-FETCH
    The JS excludes products already in cart client-side after receiving HTML.
    But Liquid renders based on what the Recommendations API returns, and the
    API doesn't know what's in the cart. So we request `limit` = displayLimit + 2
    from the API, render all of them in Liquid, then JS hides the extras.
    The simpler alternative — excluding server-side via cart object — only works
    when section is fetched in a cart context, which isn't guaranteed for cached
    CDN responses. Client-side exclusion is safer.

  SCHEMA
    Minimal schema required for section registration. No blocks needed.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    ── Resolve product_id ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Prefer the product_id URL param (set by JS). If absent, fall back to the
    last item in the active cart session. If the cart is empty, bail out early.
  endcomment

  assign recs_product_id = request.query_string | split: 'product_id=' | last | split: '&' | first | plus: 0

  if recs_product_id == 0
    if cart.items.size > 0
      assign recs_product_id = cart.items.last.product_id
    endif
  endif

  comment
    ── Resolve intent ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  endcomment
  assign recs_intent = request.query_string | split: 'intent=' | last | split: '&' | first
  if recs_intent == blank or recs_intent != 'related'
    assign recs_intent = 'complementary'
  endif

  comment
    ── Resolve limit ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Over-fetch by 2 to give JS room to hide already-carted items.
  endcomment
  assign display_limit = request.query_string | split: 'limit=' | last | split: '&' | first | plus: 0
  if display_limit == 0
    assign display_limit = 4
  endif
  assign fetch_limit = display_limit | plus: 2

  comment
    ── Build cart_item_ids for in-cart detection ────────────────────────────
    We pass this to the snippet so it can mark already-carted variants.
  endcomment
  assign cart_item_ids = ''
  for item in cart.items
    assign cart_item_ids = cart_item_ids | append: item.variant_id | append: ','
  endfor
  assign cart_item_ids = cart_item_ids | split: ','
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  ── Early exit ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  No product_id means we have nothing to base recommendations on.
  Render empty so JS can detect "no recommendations" and hide the container.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if recs_product_id == 0 -%}
  {%- comment -%} Intentionally empty — JS checks for empty response {%- endcomment -%}
{%- else -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    ── Fetch recommendations from Shopify's Product Recommendations API ──────
    `recommendations` is a Liquid object available inside section templates.
    It maps directly to the /recommendations/products endpoint.
    intent: 'complementary' surfaces accessories; 'related' is algorithm-based.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- assign recommendations = recommendations.products -%}

  {%- comment -%}
    Shopify's `recommendations` object is only populated when the section
    is rendered with the product_id in context (Section Rendering API sets
    this automatically when product_id is in the query string alongside
    section_id). The object is named `recommendations` and is scoped to this
    section render — it reads from the same endpoint used by the AJAX API.

    In practice: when JS calls:
      /?section_id=cart-recommendations&product_id=123&intent=complementary
    Shopify populates `recommendations` here with up to `fetch_limit` products.
  {%- endcomment -%}
  {%- render 'product-recommendation',
    products:       recommendations,
    cart_item_ids:  cart_item_ids,
    recs_limit:     display_limit,
    recs_title:     'You might also like'
  -%}

{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Cart Recommendations",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "display_limit",
      "label": "Number of recommendations",
      "min": 2,
      "max": 6,
      "step": 1,
      "default": 4,
      "info": "Maximum cards shown in the cart drawer. Actual count may be lower if products are already in cart."
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "intent",
      "label": "Recommendation strategy",
      "options": [
        { "value": "complementary", "label": "Complementary (accessories, add-ons)" },
        { "value": "related",       "label": "Related (similar products)" }
      ],
      "default": "complementary",
      "info": "Complementary requires manual curation in Search & Discovery app. Falls back to Related automatically if no complementary products are configured."
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}